Import Data Device +Browser- New Users

DA <-  read_excel("~/Desktop/Job related/Surefoot/Surefoot 2/Surefoot- GA/Analysis - 2/test and control dates/Device+New Users/Device+browser.xlsx", sheet = 2)

Data wrangling

DA_01 <- DA 
 names(DA)
##  [1] "Browser"                   "Device Category"          
##  [3] "Date Range"                "Segment"                  
##  [5] "Users"                     "New Users"                
##  [7] "Sessions"                  "Bounce Rate"              
##  [9] "Pages / Session"           "Avg. Session Duration"    
## [11] "Ecommerce Conversion Rate" "Transactions"             
## [13] "Revenue"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Device Category"] <- "Device" 
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Date Range"] <- "Date_Range" 
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="New Users"] <- "New_Users"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Bounce Rate"] <- "Bounce_Rate"
  

DA_02 <- DA_01 %>% filter(!is.na(Browser))

DA_03 <- DA_02 %>% mutate(test_categ = ifelse(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019", "test-Oct 18,2019 - Oct 31,2019", "control-Oct 4,2019 - Oct 17,2019"))

DC_04 <- DA_03 %>% filter(Device != "tablet")

DB_m <- DC_04 %>% filter(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019")

Visualization Device-Browser-New Users count

DA_20 <- DC_04  %>% select(Device, Browser , Revenue, test_categ)
DA_23 <- unique(DA_20)

DA_24 <- DA_23 %>% group_by(Browser, Device, test_categ) %>% mutate(TotRv = sum(Revenue)) %>% select(Browser, Device, TotRv, test_categ)
DA_25 <- unique(DA_24)

DA_25$Browser<- as.factor(DA_25$Browser) 
DA_25 %>%  filter(TotRv > 0 ) %>%
ggplot(aes(reorder(x=Browser, TotRv), y=TotRv, fill=Device)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position = "dodge")  + theme(plot.title = element_text(size =10),axis.text.x = element_text(size =7,angle = 65, hjust = 1) ) + ggtitle("Fig.1 New Users by Browser by Device ") +xlab("Browser") + ylab("Total Revenue") +  scale_fill_manual(values=c("red", "darkgreen", "springgreen1", "turquoise2", "yellow", "grey", "purple", "salmon2", "olivedrab3", "magenta2", "khaki3", "brown2", "maroon2", "coral1", "grey45", "goldenrod1", "slategray3","tan4", "orchid3", "hotpink4", "black", "brown4", "lightpink2" )) + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=3, alpha = 1))) + scale_shape_manual(values=c(3:9)) + facet_wrap(~test_categ)

Import Data Device + Hour- New Users

Data wrangling

DA_01 <- DA 
 names(DA)
##  [1] "Default Channel Grouping"  "Hour"                     
##  [3] "Date Range"                "Segment"                  
##  [5] "Users"                     "New Users"                
##  [7] "Sessions"                  "Bounce Rate"              
##  [9] "Pages / Session"           "Avg. Session Duration"    
## [11] "Ecommerce Conversion Rate" "Transactions"             
## [13] "Revenue"
colnames(DA_01)[colnames(DA_01)=="Default Channel Grouping"] <- "Channel"

 #USe of Tablet is very insignificant as compared to Desktop so Desktop and Tablet considered as #Desktop.
DA_03$Segment <- str_replace(DA_03$Segment, "Tablet and Desktop Traffic", "Desktop")
DA_03$Segment <- str_replace(DA_03$Segment, "Mobile Traffic", "Mobile")

#filter out Tablet rows
DA_04 <-DA_03 %>% filter(Segment != "Tablet Traffic")


DH_m <- DA_04 %>% filter(Date_Range == "Oct 18, 2019 - Oct 31, 2019")

Visualization

DA_20 <- DA_04 %>% select(test_categ, Segment,  Hour, Revenue)

DA_25 <- unique(DA_24)

ggplot(aes(reorder(x=Segment, TotRev), y=TotRev, fill=Hour)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position = "dodge")  + theme(plot.title = element_text(size =10),axis.text.x = element_text(size =7,angle = 45, hjust = 1) ) + ggtitle("Fig. 6 New Users by Hour by Device ")  +xlab("Device") + ylab("Total Revenue") +  scale_fill_manual(values=c("red", "darkgreen", "springgreen1", "turquoise2", "yellow", "grey", "purple", "salmon2", "olivedrab3", "magenta2", "khaki3", "brown2", "maroon2", "coral1", "grey45", "goldenrod1", "slategray3","tan4", "orchid3", "hotpink4", "black", "brown4", "lightpink2" )) + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size=3, alpha = 1))) + scale_shape_manual(values=c(3:9)) + facet_wrap(~test_categ)

Linear Regression

model_01x <- lm(Revenue ~ Browser+Device+New_Users+Bounce_Rate+Transactions , data = DB_m)
#summary(model_01x)
a<- data.frame(summary(model_01x)$coef[summary(model_01x)$coef[,4] <= .05, 4])
colnames(a) <- c("p-value")
a

## BrowserChrome 7.094078e-09

## Transactions  8.416353e-15
